1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:06,000
Your cells run on tiny ancient power plants — and they have their own DNA.

2
00:00:06,000 --> 00:00:12,000
Meet mitochondria, the energy factories that convert food into fuel, powering every move you make.

3
00:00:12,000 --> 00:00:15,600
But here’s the twist: They were once free-living bacteria.

4
00:00:15,600 --> 00:00:17,600
Yes, you heard that right!

5
00:00:17,600 --> 00:00:24,800
This endosymbiotic theory explains how they became essential to our cells, merging with us over billions of years.

6
00:00:24,800 --> 00:00:31,600
So next time you feel energized, remember — it’s those ancient power plants working hard for you.

7
00:00:31,600 --> 00:00:33,600
Curious about more science secrets?

8
00:00:33,600 --> 00:00:35,600
Like and follow for more!
